<h1 id="fonts">FONTS</h1>
<p><strong>bold words</strong></p>
<p><em>italic words</em></p>
<p><strong>bold</strong>then<strong>roman</strong></p>
<p>roman<em>then</em>italic</p>
<p><strong>bold</strong><em>italic</em><strong>pairs</strong></p>
<p>plain <strong>bold</strong> and <em>italic</em> and
<em><strong>both</strong></em> back to plain</p>
<p>nested <strong>outer</strong> <em>inner</em> still bold
<em>done</em></p>
<p>a font macro called with an explicit empty argument keeps its
wrapper: <strong></strong></p>
